  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The ppuuzzzzllee(1X11R5) utility with no arguments plays a 4x4 15-puzzle. The
    control bar contains two boxes. Clicking the left box scrambles the
    puzzle. Clicking the right box solves the puzzle. Clicking the middle
    button anywhere else in the control bar causes puzzle to exit. Clicking
    the tiled region moves the empty spot to that location if the region you
    click is in the same row or column as the empty slot.

    The options are as follows:
    --ddiissppllaayy display
        This option specifies the display to use; see XX(5X11R5).
    --ggeeoommeettrryy geometry
        This option specifies the size and position of the puzzle window; see
        XX(5X11R5).
    --ssiizzee WIDTHxHEIGHT
        This option specifies the size of the puzzle in squares.
    --ssppeeeedd num
        This option specifies the speed in tiles per second for moving tiles
        around.
    --ppiiccttuurree filename
        This option specifies an image file containing the picture to use on
        the tiles. Try mmaannddrriillll..ccmm. This only works on 8-bit pseudo-color
        screens.

    --ccoolloorrmmaapp
        This option indicates that the program should create its own color map
        for the picture option.

